    "url": "https://docs.python.org/3/library/symtable.html#module-symtable#symtable.Symbol.is_free_class",
    "parameters": [],
    "return_type": "",
    "exceptions": [],
    "description": "Return True if a class-scoped symbol is free from the perspective of a method. Consider the following example: def f(): x = 1 # function-scoped class C: x = 2 # class-scoped def method(self): return x In this example, the class-scoped symbol x is considered to be free from the perspective of C.method, thereby allowing the latter to return 1 at runtime and not 2. Added in version 3.14.",
    "example": "",
    "articles": [],
    "info": {
